DURBAN - Two ward Councillors from Ingwe Local Municipality were arrested for corruption by members of the Hawks Anti-Corruption Task Team in KwaZulu-Natal. Bongekile Dlamini (39) and Zamambo Mkhize (33) were illegally receiving social grants from South Africa Social Security Agency (SASSA). They were arrested and charged for corruption. SASSA lost almost R35 000. On Tuesday they appeared in the Durban Specialised Commercial Crime Court and were each granted R2 000 bail. The case was postponed to 3 June 2017. Meanwhile, the former mayor, Nomagugu Luzulane (42) and former Municipal Manager, Nthabiseng Brown (36) also appeared in the Durban Specialised Commercial Crime Court on Friday. They were charged for fraud and corruption related to the misuse of municipality funds at Ingwe Local Municipality. Brown was further charged for fraud after she allegedly submitted a false qualification. Their case was postponed to 9 June 2017.